<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="94.[107,637,634,1749]" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">
DIAGNOSIS: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; CLOSE Lorenzo Prendini Scorpion Systematics Research Group, 2017" authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[284,521,799,823]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[284,521,799,823]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">Physoctonus striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[539,632,800,823]" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differs from its sister species, 
<taxonomicName box="[452,546,832,856]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[452,546,832,856]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as follows. The mesosomal tergites of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[483,595,866,889]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[483,595,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are dark, with transverse bands of infuscation, whereas the tergites of 
<taxonomicName box="[373,467,931,955]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[373,467,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are uniformly pale, except for the infuscate dorsomedian carinae, which form a thin stripe longitudinally. The carinae of the carapace, pedipalps, and metasoma are less pronounced in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName box="[549,624,1064,1087]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stria">P. stria</taxonomicName>
- tus
</emphasis>
than in 
<taxonomicName box="[246,343,1097,1121]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[246,343,1097,1121]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: for example, the lateral inframedian carinae of metasomal segments II and III are restricted to the posterior third of the segment in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[292,405,1197,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[292,405,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but complete in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and the retromedian and secondary accessory carinae of the pedipalp chela manus are vestigial to absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[402,514,1296,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[402,514,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but complete and granular in 
<taxonomicName box="[356,451,1328,1352]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[356,451,1328,1352]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Pedipalp chela fixed finger trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[433,461,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">db</emphasis>
is aligned with trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[300,321,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">et</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lauren A. Esposito &amp; Humberto Y. Yamaguti &amp; Cláudio A. Souza &amp; Ricardo Pinto-Da-Rocha &amp; Lorenzo Prendini" authorityYear="2017" box="[367,484,1395,1418]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[367,484,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but situated distal to 
<emphasis box="[209,229,1428,1451]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">et</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[269,364,1427,1451]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Physoctonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="94" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[269,364,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">P. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="94" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="94.[107,637,634,1749]" pageId="94" pageNumber="94">ETYMOLOGY: The species name refers to the transverse bands of infuscation on the mesosomal tergites.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
